   Experience Le Burgundy Paris

Le Burgundy Paris, city's most lavish hotel

A place that is both contemporary and yet also timeless

   The classic décor of the hotel Le Burgundy Paris embodies ageless
   Parisian chic and blends it with an innovative modernity. The past and
   the present are seamlessly unified as the creators of today reinvent
   the expertise of yesterday. Cosy and intimate, the atmosphere of this
   hotel has real warmth, enhanced by the talents of the artists and
   artisans who have poured their hearts into its realization.

A hotel that is the very epitome of fashion and luxury awaits your stay

   Indeed, the hotel Le Burgundy Paris occupies a prestigious location at
   the very heart of an eminently fashionable district. A short stroll
   will take you to the establishments of the master jewelers of the place
   Vendôme, the legendary boutiques of the place de la Madeleine and the
   upmarket retail opportunities to be found within the shops of the rue
   Saint-Honoré. Le Burgundy is well placed amidst this elegance and
   offers a superb selection of luxurious rooms and exclusive suites, an
   ultra-chic bar and a superior restaurant along with fully customised
   services to delight even the most discerning of guests
   Our packages
   spa by sothys

Take your time at the Spa by Sothys

   In this elegant space away from the hustle and bustle, everything has
   been designed to make your experience a unique moment.
   A harmony of noble materials combined with warm inviting relaxation,
   rest of the body and the abandonment of the senses...
   Read more
   News

Pastries to go at Le Burgundy Paris

   Le Burgundy Paris is proud to announce that from now on, pastries from
   Pastry Chef Pascal Hainigue, will be available to order and take away.

   In an elegant white and gold packaging, with a pattern referring to the
   sculpture of Guy de Rougemont decorating the floor of Le Burgundy
   Paris’ lobby, pastries can be purchased individually or with 4 or more
   pieces, upon request.

   You will find Pascal Hainigue's classics, such as the Arriba Chocolate
   Tartlet 75% with caramel and vanilla flowing heart, the Religieuse with
   spicy caramel, praline almond, tonka bean, or the Shiso-pineapple.
   Other seasonal creations will complete the offer throughout the year
   ...

   Prepared every day in the laboratory of Pascal Hainigue, pastries are
   edited in limited quantities.

   From € 8  to 12 a piece

   Information and orders at:

   +33 (0) )1 71 19 49 11

   or directly from your room.


